<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0deb2c3e-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413"><num value="4413">§ 4413.</num><heading> Executive Board</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0deb2c3f-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Composition</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Board shall have an Executive Board composed of—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0deb2c40-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the chairman of the Board;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0deb2c41-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the vice chairman of the Board;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0deb2c42-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the secretary of the Board;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0deb2c43-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> the treasurer of the Board; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0deb2c44-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/a/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> an at-large member of the Board elected by the Board at its initial meeting.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0deb2c45-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Vacancies</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the case of any vacancy which occurs in the position of at-large member before the expiration of such member’s term, the Board shall elect a replacement to complete that term.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0deb2c46-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Meetings</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Executive Board shall hold not more than 4 regular meetings per calendar year. Special meetings may be held upon the call of the chairman or 3 members of the Executive Board.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0deb2c47-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/d"><num value="d" class="bold">(d)</num><heading class="bold"> Quorum</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A majority of the Executive Board shall constitute a quorum.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0deb2c48-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4413/e"><num value="e" class="bold">(e)</num><heading class="bold"> Powers</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Executive Board may hold and use all the powers of the Board, subject to the approval of the Board.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0deb2c49-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/498/tXV/s1506">Pub. L. 99–498, title XV, § 1506</ref>, <date date="1986-10-17">Oct. 17, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1603">100 Stat. 1603</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
